{"_id":"6FakIhUSBCtNTKZV","name":"02 - History of Zalos","content":"<div class=\"coriolis-community-atlas-journal-entry\">\n<h1>HISTORY OF ZALOS</h1>\n<p>The origins of The Order date back to the exodus from the Second Horizon by a group of dogmatic warrior monks. They called themselves the Order of the Pariah, having been cast out because of their fervent faith in the Martyr as the ultimate saviour of humankind.</p>\n<p>They were drawn to Zalos because of the celestial phenomenon that is now known as “The Crown of the Martyr”, a system-wide solar wind said to enhance prophetic visions. The Order believed (and continues to believe) that the Crown is the Martyr leading his followers to a home among the stars. Over the centuries, The Order has turned the entire system into a temple dedicated the Icon.</p>\n<p>Very little is known about the early years of The Order, only that the deep faith that burns within the hearts of Zalosians today burned bright even then. Zalosians were heavily involved in the Portal Wars, raising the banners of the Martyr and singing to his glory beneath skies of blood and fire. There was no doubt that they alone were the true faithful.</p>\n<p>During the war, the Zalosian system went into full lockdown while her holy warriors waged their bloody crusade across the Horizon. After the Long Night, The Order grudgingly joined the emergent empires of the Third Horizon and took up a seat at the Council of Factions on Coriolis, relaying the warnings from their prophets about the return of darkness and strife.</p>\n<p>In CC60, the Emissaries of Xene appeared. Overnight, Zalos recalled their ambassadors home and locked down their system once more – a chilling echo of the old war. Zalos is now under complete lockdown by The Martyr Fleet, which performs extensive system-wide monitoring and patrol operations. The only route not closed to visitors is the one leading to the City of Foreigners on Karrmerruk. The Martyr Fleet’s presence is heaviest around Zahedan to stop rebels from leaving the planet.</p></div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9lJzeDMf24iRID0x":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"08 - Places of Interest","content":"<div class=\"coriolis-community-atlas-journal-entry\">\n<h1>PLACES OF INTEREST</h1>\n<h2>HALLS OF KORAZAN</h2>\n<p>The largest trade deals always take place in the Halls of Korazan, located on the outskirts of the commerce district, next to the spaceport. It is a large complex of halls and warehouses solely devoted to foreign trade, each of which takes on the distinct attributes of the wares traded there.</p>\n<p>For instance, 'The Basin' is characterized by a smell of salt and seaweed, and loud merchants auctioning off large hauls of exotic fish from the Zalosian oceans. The green market is characterized by the chirping of birds and the murmuring negotiations of merchants, while deals for the precious metals used in ship propulsion systems are made in a heavily guarded area known as The Forge. Agents from the Draconite faction have been seen here, making deals on minerals and silicates used for their terrifying Meson weaponry.</p>\n<h2>THE SOUK OF MISTS</h2>\n<p>The Souk of Mists is located under the City of Foreigner’s second-largest dome, named after the constant fog that covers the bazaar at the center of the district, as well as the surrounding blocks. The souk is a bustling marketplace with narrow alleys and tiny plazas. Visitors from all across the Horizon can mingle with the locals here, take a break in the small Kawah shops or listen to the street musicians. Several stores and restaurants are run by outsiders, who have sworn fealty to the Martyr and provide the residents of the moon with food and products not manufactured in the Zalos system. The magistrates keep a constant vigil in this district, as the Souk is deemed to be a prime target for the heretics of Zahedan.</p>\n<h2>THE 11TH OSSUARY</h2>\n<p>The smallest dome of the city houses the 11th Ossuary. This is one of the largest bone chambers in the system, but its halls are barren compared to the ancient ossuaries on Zalos. Very few inhabitants are actually born on Karrmerruk, and their remains are usually brought back to Zalos. Instead, the 11th Ossuary houses the remains of notable prophets, brave martyrs and mighty generals from the Portal Wars.</p>\n<p>There are plenty of rumours surrounding the ossuary, the most persistent one claims that it contains the bones of actual portal builders. Anyone foolish enough to utter these rumors in the City of Foreigners can expect a visit from the Magistrates.</p>\n<h2>THE HAMMER OF THE MARTYR</h2>\n<p>The battlecruiser “The Hammer of the Martyr” keeps an endless vigil above the city. The giant ship is a constant reminder of the strength and technological superiority of The Martyr Fleet, with its mighty towers, spires and weapon systems. Its hull is covered by glyph armor, a marvelous invention that constantly shifts in fractal structures, causing severe headaches to the unfamiliar observer. The aft features a glowing sphere contained by a contraption shaped like a horse-shoe: the much sought after antimatter drive that is far superior to the technologies used by other factions in the Horizon.</p></div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"nRie7LEo31St9hvS":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.T4K69Y5BLV1RKOwT"}},"_id":"9Om3p3Qca5Wrzg7N"}
{"_id":"LLT7lJouXahXDEcQ","name":"00 - Zalos","content":"<div class=\"coriolis-community-atlas-journal-entry\">\n<h1>Zalos</h1>\n<h3><em> Zalos – the home of the Martyrs. The Order of the Pariah reigns here, known for both its pious monks and its bloodthirsty fanatics. It is an inhospitable system that treats strangers with suspicion and whose leaders go to great lengths to protect their population from external influence. </em></h3>\n<h2>Index</h2>\n<p>@JournalEntry[qGkFDUgiwJLSFYL7]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[6FakIhUSBCtNTKZV]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[moPB0kYSObjsZVrE]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[y6duw45NRsJtCmRT]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[iIiyxrEEpCHl1EBN]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[mEOIfkh4oAjgY9LY]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[xQyREEKW3qxypOhZ]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[9Om3p3Qca5Wrzg7N]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[P9Ms5drwYWm3RQAb]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[zCqppTzhSQ4cHnr2]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[egriIWmR1oS1eiCB]</p>\n<p>@JournalEntry[lb2EiEa5Yb1Nx9FC]</p>\n</div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"nRie7LEo31St9hvS":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.coriolis-community-atlas.zalos_journals.jDcztmk50TcaOklh"}}}
